In a fraction of a second, it's your turn.
After a short moment, an old couple arrives to inquire about the rent, but the new rents do not seem to concern people in the waiting room.
The majority of people came to solve common problems like everywhere - demand for repairs, insurance events and others.
In the Ostrava region, people in more than 44,000 RPG apartments have been receiving mail with new lease contracts in their mailbox since about mid-November.
RPG Byty offers rent increases from 15 to 38 percent.
The special locker for new rents has been open to the public since November 18.
"It's been working for almost a week, so it's still testing," replies, after a moment of hesitation, the employee behind the box office when the client presents himself as a journalist.
Deragulation and the old miner apartments in Bakal are a very sensitive local topic.
The Vice-President of Parliament and native of the Ostrava region Lubomir Zaoralek of the Social Democrats reported this in a fairly sustained manner before the elections and this now fills the local newspapers.
“Twenty years later, I want a new floor.”
"They didn't even change me a put...n board in the toilets, is relieved in introduction the man mentioned.
However, these are mostly, according to employees, retirees who come to make sure they will receive a return on the new rent price if they sign now as RPG promised in a special offer.
