And yet RPG puts individual interviews on rents on both its website and in the windows when necessary.
If the two parties do not agree on the rent, it is an independent court that will make the decision.
“These are not threats, but only to inform about the unique and legitimate way to act legally,” RPG said on its website.
"Here no one will go to court," thinks one of RPG employees Byty and the man on the street in front of the customer center gives her right.
