Builders and architects have the opportunity to combine a careful work for children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who imagined this kindergarten and with the support of the management they were able to obtain a grant from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini kindergarten is funded from the European Social Fund through the Human Resources Operational Program and the Czech State Budget.
Thanks to the funding allocations (up to 2.8 million Czech crowns). They were able to purchase equipment and equipment and after two years to ensure qualified personnel as well as start-up.
After the use of the funding allocation (two years) the company Arch. Design. has an obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The project prepared for a year and it was the Economy rating company that helped apply for staffing.
Children's care is provided by qualified staff, all day a nurse and a nurse care for the children. children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they are over three for most.
