In the building of the Land Fund in Plzen, anti-corruption police have been arresting in recent days.
The detectives passed the handcuffs to the local contractor and real estate trader Lubos.
The latter had endeavoured to manipulate a public tender for the settlement of a refund application in such a way that the proposed land was obtained by a specific candidate.
This one had to pay Lubos G. half a million crowns.
"For now I can only confirm that the police are prosecuting a person for insider crime in the context of a public tender and competition," said the head of the Prosecutor's Office of Plzen Antonie Zelena for the Pravo newspaper, knowing that it is forbidden to provide further explanations because the investigation is ongoing.
The police released this 46-year-old entrepreneur after 24 hours.
To find out how it could influence a public competition, one can only speculate on the basis of so little official information.
Asked by Pravo, the spokeswoman for the Lubomira Cerna Land Fund said the police had actually carried out an arrest in Plzen in a separate workplace during the public competition.
"It was a client and under no circumstances an employee," she said.
The real name of the public competition according to Cerna is "Call to propose rights for land transfers under the Land Act" and is set up when several law-beneficiary candidates manifest themselves.
"These persons offer, in the context of the appeal, a higher value of their entitlements to restitutions that must be settled before the value of the land is announced."
“According to the proposed rights, a ranking of buyers is set up and the Land Fund then transfers the land to the person who proposed the highest rights,” said the Fund’s spokesman.
Lubos G. had, it is clear, information about the persons who had registered for the appeal and as he himself is also a beneficiary because having purchased a large number of entitlements to refunds, he had offered the field candidates not to participate in the competition.
