The U.S. military sent a new "smart" weapon to Afghanistan, known only as the XM-25 code.
Generals believe that this new automatic rifle will have an influence on the conflict there with the Taliban and “will change the game” for their benefit.
The new weapon is like a super precise gun.
Its projectiles are guided by laser with a precision of a few meters.
The special 25 mm caliber ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly breaking explosive, actually functions like small grenades.
The ammunition can be programmed in such a way that it will explode at contact with the target but also at any point in their ballistic trajectory.
