So far, the inspectors have not indicated which facilities are here, what is their function or what is suspected to contain them.
According to information published by the Süddeutsche Zeitung, they are known within the IAEA respectively as Marj as-Sultan, Masyaf and Iskandariayah also from the names of neighboring cities.
The independent Institute for Science and International Security in Washington identified these locations and discovered on satellite images a complex near Masyaf that would most likely be one of the suspicious objects.
It is possible that it is located on or directly next to a military base; this is exactly the reason why Syria refuses access to the three sites to IAEA inspectors.
